        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 7:29PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 729 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
North La Junta, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
La Junta, North La Junta, Las Animas, John Martin Reservoir, and Fort
Lyon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
